name: Block Party
description: Start low on a jug and follow blocks to the top out

name: Bouldering For Dummies
description: Start low on a jug in the center of the cave on the left. Work backward along the blocs and top out through the middle of the overhang.

name: Golden Curry
description: Start on undercling in center/right side of the cave on the right side and follow out to the top out on the right

name: gringo
description: sit start two-handed side puls in the middle of the cave move left and up to top out

name: The Horizontal Schnitzel
description: Follow the lowest level of rock from left to right while you keep your feet as high as possible. If you want to, you can "run out" the over hang into an easier face climb all the way to the right until there is no rock anymore. When grabbing only the crimps, it's a long crimp endurance boulder with a few fancy kneel hocks.  You either need a lot of crash pads or someone who moves them for you while you boulder.

name: Jam Boi
description: Start on a side pull low and to the right in the left cave move through moderate holds and pull the blocks to top out

name: closing statement
description: on the right side of the cave start matched on the pinch. move up and to the right to top out

name: the prosecution
description: the left side of the cave start on the obvious start jug and go straight up and out the cave

name: hivvy ivvy
description: start on a slot crimp move up and to the left for a spicy top out

name: the last puppy
description: start on lower ledge move up under the roof compressing the sides to pull straight out the middle

name: Redemption
description: Start low on a left side pull and work right through a right-handed gaston towards the top

name: Chest Trap
description: Start on a matched chest high crimp and follow pockets and crimps toward the top out

name: easy feasy
description: start low left then more right and up easy holds up the left side

name: I Hate Spiders
description: match start on a pocket at eye level  uses the crimps and pockets to climb all the way to the top

name: pho
description: start on the lower left corner use moderate holds with big moves to top out

name: when i put my climbing shoes on i become like super man
description: start matches on an under cling  compression use slopy crimps and pockets to top out

name: Country Girls
description: Best boulder in the overlook area and the biggest. Has potential for multiple lines.

name: Fossil Boulder
description: Starts on right side of the bottom following the lip to the top.

name: Hidalgo
description: bad landing, but solid hang problem

name: All Quiet on the Western Front
description: A powerful route with a solid arête on the right with slopers and a sharp pocket on the left.

name: Cut Your Teeth
description: Sit start to some decent jugs before working the arêtes to the top. Avoiding the chipped crimpers around to the far right keeps the climbing more consistent and engaging.

name: Phallic in the Fall
description: Compression holds on good arêtes with an decent smears and heel hooks. Somewhat continuous which earns a v2 grade. Avoiding the obvious chipped crimps around the right arête (mural side of the rock) is the best way and makes for a much more rewarding climb.

name: The South Face
description: Balance is key. Sit start on the right side and work up through a couple v3 moves to a decent stance under the small overhang, then its small edges, and tiny slopers to the top. The arêtes are there but it is a better climb if you don't use them.

name: Zero Rock
description: Massive pockets lend themselves to uninspiring climbing. Good for warming up or for a confidence booster if the other problems are shutting you down. There could possibly be a line on the south face of this rock, avoiding the arêtes, which would definitely not be a v0.

name: Andre's Dong
description: On the side of the wall facing away from the water on the far right side their are blocks sticking out forming a kind of staircase arrangement. This route is also the easiest to down climb which will be required once you top out.

name: Davey Jones' Mum
description: Climb up around the back side of the wall starting down by the water and climb up until you can reach the metal bar and then just shimmy across to the other side where there is some other weird stuff to mess around on. Go for foot work practice or you can let go of the metal and try and find actual holds on the way but if you fall the water is only about a foot deep and their is some metal and rock at the bottom so I don't recommend falling on this side of the wall!

name: Humble Beginnings
description: Far left side of the wall facing away from the water another staircase like structure. Easiest to down climb the far right side of the wall (Andre's Dong V1)

name: Blimey!
description: Traverse from right to left along cliff, about 20ft. There is horizontal cracks that run the full length of the climb for tiny hand holds. Almost no feet to start with (and difficult feet to find for the remainder) and the crux is a cool cross to lieback move within the first 3 moves. We have to work with what we got around kansas, so no cheating and using the top of cliff (though, just using the top makes a nice VB warm-up) or pulling off choss for better foot holds!     !Yemilb is the same traverse but from left to right. It is slightly more difficult because the crux is at the end when you're nicely pumped out. The moves and slightly different holds are actually a bit more interesting than the original right to left version.

name: Paris's Arrow
description: Cool, but sadly very short problem. Start low with a big heel hook to a tiny crack. Match, then move to next tiny crack and finish with an easy mantle.

name: Max's Traverse
description: 10 ft traverse from right to left (though left to right is nearly identical). The hand holds are very solid and are mostly in the horizontal cracks that run the length of the route, but feet can be crumbly. The route was originally done on only the gray rock for extra challenge and to avoid the crumbly yellow stuff at the very bottom. No real crux, fairly solid moves and holds throughout the WHOLE 10ft! We have to work with what we got here in kansas, so no using the top or pulling off choss.

name: Feeling Desparate
description: Sit start at the base of the overhanging arete with a good right hand and a sharp left hand crimp. The route goes straight up the arete to a nice jug for the topout.

name: brunch time arete
description: start on a left side pull crimp and a 2 finger pocket follow the arete to the top

name: crimp grits
description: lets pull on some crimps

name: Grandma's Biscuits
description: Climb the arete, moving into the slab face of the wall.

name: Huevos Rancheros
description: Start left and right paw on crimps. Right hand up to a pinch or sloppy side-pull, left will go find a nubbin. Catch the lip. Considerably better rock quality than the other face. Will clean up over time.  Stay on the line, arete is off, the face has a nice flow to it, enjoy.

name: Wavy gravy
description: Start no hands use pockets to top out

name: Rona ledge Stand
description: Start matched on a hold just outside where the top boulder stops covering the bottom boulder. Use a toe jam in the crack or low feet to move left hand out and do balance moves to top out. All holds seem stable, which is very rare for the area, and not too sharp  Very much so opportunity to start half way in cave ledge (probably around v6) or farther for harder.

name: A Crack House in Kansas
description: a stunning roof problem where your feet are the most important thing! start on the rail at the back of the cave move up and to the right then moving into the crack to pull the crux moves to top out.

name: adiós mis dos dedos
description: start on the large jug rail pull 2 finger pockets to a high step committing move then use larger holds to top out

name: Mellow Yellow Fellow
description: Follow rail to the right into the crack. from the top of the crack work to the right through obvious jugs

name: Elk City Sidepull
description: Slopey crimps lead up to a good horizontals. Once past the horizontals, climb pockety jugs to the top.

name: Lightning Bolt Flakes
description: Start just right of the easy corner, using small edges to move up to some horizontals. After placing some gear, move up past the huge creaky flake. I yarded on this flake quite a bit before leading the route and it didn't fall off. However, it flexes quite a bit and is huge, so I didn't pull on it while climbing. It is easy to avoid, so you might just want to do that. The upper part of the route is fairly juggy, but it is quite a ways down to your last piece, so keep it together. There is a flake you can place a questionable C4 #.75 behind, as well as a pass-thru that can be threaded.

name: Meadowlark Perch
description: Boulder up on to a ledge to gain a crack system. Follow the narrowing crack to the top.

name: Unknown 4 Bolt Sport Route
description: Climb up slab doing reachy moves past 4 bolts. You can top this climb out, but there is loose rock above the last bolt, so be cautious.

name: free willy
description: start on the lower sloper rail move up and to the right using the pockets on the top to top out

name: Kansas coral
description: start on the sloper rail pull the undercling and climb the crack

name: lay down
description: start on the sloper rail pull the under cling then use pockets and tec to top out

name: the lean back
description: start on the sloper rail move up and a hair to your right

name: La Chica Buena
description: This is a fun and exposed route. Start on a couple of short boulders on the hiking trail. The beginning has a little bit of chossy rock but is mostly clear. Follow a crack up and right to a north facing wall and cruse to the top. This route could eventually be a trad route if somebody doesn't get sketched out by the runout at the beginning.

name: Yates city danger
description: a dangerous route with compression moves near the top

name: Better with Jam
description: Starts in the middle of the lower two rocks. A deep hand jam may be helpful. Goes straight up for the challenging top out

name: Toe Jam
description: Far left sds with a hand jam and and toe jam if you so chose

name: Hookers to the Left
description: Start low on the far right and quickly get to the top and traverse left using a series of heel hooks. Use the slightly unstable ledge on the far left to plant a foot for a unique top out.

name: Hookers to the Right
description: This starts on the flake to the far left and traverses via heel hooks to the right and finishing on the start of Hookers to the Left

name: Back Burner
description: Starts on medium sized rock in the center of the west side of boulder. This route head straight upward and then deviates to the left with an obvious top out.

name: Fracker's Traverse
description: This route starts on the southwest arete and shares the same start as What the Elk and Got Driftwood. It follows a leftward traverse low then over the middle bulge (starts for Popped my Cherry and Backburner) then gradually trends upward to the very top left corner.

name: Got Driftwood?
description: Shares the same starting hold and finish as What the Elk. Quickly moves out left and up to the piece of driftwood.

name: Popped my Cherry
description: Shares the same start as Back Burner and move up and to the right where is shares the same finish as What the Elk and Got Driftwood.

name: What the Elk?
description: Starts at the soutwest arete on a bridging of 2 layers of rock. SDS that follows the left side of the arete and exits near the piece of driftwood. This route shares the same start as Got Driftwood and Fracker's Traverse

name: Above the Belt
description: crash pad

name: Below the Belt
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: Crack to the Future
description: Starts in the crack just beneath the downward pointing "beak". Traverses right and finishes out the same as The Cracken

name: The Cracken
description: Starting on the far left corner traverse right across the horizontal to meet up with Up the Crack

name: Left the Crack Alone
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: On the Hip
description: Starts on far left side and goes straight up the arete.

name: Seams Ok
description: Starts right of the vertical crack and traverses the seam above the horizontal crack and finishes out on the top left

name: Son of a Beach
description: Starts far left of boulder and then straight up for finish

name: Up the Crack
description: Starts at the vertical crack

name: Kansas City Shuffle
description: Climbs the north end of the Piano

name: Pole Dancer
description: starts on the right side of the piano boulder. Don't dab on the pole just dance around it

name: Heal Hookin Hooker
description: A large traverse with plenty of heel hooks

name: Hole In The Wall
description: a short problem that goes through a hole in the top

name: Throw a Fist
description: An easy move to an unnecessary fist jam

name: Blake
description: Start on the far right of the rock there will be good deep jugs as you make your way right. Good luck finding good foot holds, you have to grab a crimp to the left and then top out.

name: Eye of the Rona
description: Exact same as Eye of the Rona direct however a toe hook on the left side of the boulder is encouraged to use to adjust hands and reach the top. Video for beta -> youtu.be/X74_zMojlRI

name: Eye of the Rona Direct
description: Start in the circular hold and after adjusting hands throw upwards and top out. DO NOT use the rock near the ground or any toe hooks, this is to be on the face of the rock only. Video of the send -> https://youtu.be/DNV1uOghJMw

name: Rona Ring
description: Starts low on the left side of the small entrance boulder and traverses around to the right side of the boulder and tops out. Video for beta -> https://youtu.be/_TowArpc5zU

name: Taming Wolves
description: Big moves to pretty deep, sharp holds. Two cruxes, in the middle there is a large move to a right hand and topping out is hard without good beta. Rock quality is good but has some choss. In general all of the moves create a fun route which is pretty long (about 12 moves). video for beta -> https://youtu.be/KToo9Qq0vy4  Update: hold used for topping out has broken off, still a reasonable climb though

name: Taming Wolves Left
description: Starts to the left of Taming Wolves deep in the boulder. Links into Taming Wolves after a few moves. Fun problem but the rock can be chossy. The top hold to top out has been broken off but that is not a huge deal. Video of the send but cut off at the end -> youtu.be/tW47JQXsKUU

name: Taming Wolves-The Radical Left Variation
description: An even more radically left variation to taming wolves. Sit start on the far left side of the prow on the jugs at the bottom of the rail. Move right using heel and toe hooks, a peculiar mono, and other forms of wizardry to join back into "Taming Wolves Left". If this has already been done please comment and I will update.

name: Dodge City
description: Start on a crappy left hand pinch and a good right hand crimp. From there work your way to the right up to some powerful moves near the top. Finish on the lip near the top. Haven’t cleaned the topout yet.

name: Wheaties in the Wheat field
description: Start on a big jug undercling and throw up to a beautifully sculpted sharp pocket. From there work your way up and to the right on a spicy topout. Be sure to bring some grit to this one.

name: John-dito
description: start left hand on a small jug and right on under cling pinch go up to the obvious sloper and crimp bump left then go big right to a jug then top out

name: favorite little place
description: start on the Southside pillar climb up and slightly to the left grabbing a small left edge on the cap and going straight up.

name: Lizard Life
description: Located near the back of Mushroom State park opposite of restrooms.

name: Shirtless
description: Start on the right side and basically dyno to the top.

name: Quarantine Left Traverse
description: On the face of the house, start on the left corner pillar, traverse across some crimps and tough balance parts. Finish is a pin in the doorframe with both hands on the large white headstone above the door.

name: Assent
description: Start with the opposing side pulls. Top out making the best of the slopers and/or pinches that recede toward the top of the spherical boulder.  Note: I do not claim to be the "developer" of this route. It looks pretty straightforward, even aside from the chalk marks left from previous climbers on the side pulls and jugs. I am only posting this description for two reasons: so that others will be on the look out for this fun route and so that others can add their opinions about its difficulty/rating/etc.

name: Close contact
description: Foot edges on the light colored rock beneath, RH sloper, LH square sloper above, match, twist to adjacent boulder to the L around using obvious ledges there, use pinches and jugs to get to the top of that boulder; come back down across the back of the first boulder

name: Daddy's Home
description: This problem is on one of the larger boulders that are clustered together away from the main parking area.    This route starts maybe twenty feet to the right of "Close Contact.". Find an obvious zig zagging crack on the face of this boulder and move maybe seven feet to the right of that crack. The problem ascends the boulder on crimps. The white/grey shelf below the boulder is off.

name: Eye sockets
description: Two hand start with the two pockets

name: Friendly Face Tannenbaum
description: Start left hand side pull under finger pocket, right hand in right eye of “frowny face”. Can use mono but it’s rough pull. Left foot in bottom crack under side pull. Bump right to three finger pocket, right foot crack under. Semi dyno to good crimp near top, stand into worse crimp above mono. Reach over and top out!

name: Get the hang of it
description: Start low at the base, LH jug in large crack, match, RH sidepull in same crack, RH sloper at the intersection of the three cracks, LH crimp on a very small knob above, then use obvious jugs and ledges and top out; come down from the other side of the boulder (in part using the adjacent one).

name: I Like Turtles
description: One move wonder. Start matched on the flat ledge and use the good foot to dyno up to the sloper. Match and go to the top. A bit contrived due to the crack out to the left being off, but a fun climb regardless.

name: Left Socket
description: Probably done before, but a fun little problem I put up while passing through Kansas. Start left of Eye sockets with your right hand in the left socket and a heel hook. Move up to a horizontal slot and then up through underclings to top out. Crux is not dabbing since you start real low.

name: Look ma no hands
description: To the L of 'Unknown' route on same boulder. Starting low, smear and match on large jug, then jump to large pocket on top with RH; left heel hook on a ledge, then use the first jug to top out. Get down from the R side of the boulder or jump off

name: Owen
description: so named for "Owen" scrawled into the boulder near the start.

name: Rolling Stones
description: Start on the boulder called "the Lips" in the yellow pamphlet given by the gift shop. Hands start on the bottom lips, and go up and slightly left.

name: The Underbelly
description: Steepest climb at Rock City? Start sitting under the short over hang, left hand on a small crimp and right hand on a sloper. Throw a right heel and make a hard move to a jug. Top out. Very low ball, but a fun, challenging move.

name: Unknown V1
description: Fun low ball crack traverse. Start matched as low as possible in the crack and then work your way up and right.

name: Wahquahboshkuk
description: May have been done before. Let me know, and I will change what is needed.

name: White cracker
description: Star your feet on a small crack beneath the mouth bring your left leg up try and get your foot into the eye on the right and step up and top out

name: Full Sus
description: Far right on boulder. Go straight up slopers and ledges to top.

name: desolation creation
description: starts on right side of face. perfectly vertical. Side pull and crimp up to some tiny pockets.

name: the smell
description: start on the lower ledge use the under cling in the roof to pull the lip

name: Whispering Water
description: Start matched on the right side on a low jug rail. Hit a right handed crimp on the right side of the block and work around for the top out

name: the wrath of Dao
description: start on the lower ledge then move out the left side of the roof

name: A new chapter
description: Sit start bottom right, then up and left on diagonal rail.

name: Chuckie
description: Funny sit start in corner

name: Done
description: Up the left side of boulder.

name: The final line of this chapter...
description: traverse rail just left of dead tree, around corner and top the same as 2... my final project at the part, and projected for 2 years before completing...

name: New breath
description: Sit start straight up

name: Pizza and snakes
description: Just left of prior

name: The start of a lifetime of smiles
description: Climb the middle line up the boulder.  My dad and I’s First boulder problem...

name: Smell of Lilly’s
description: Traverse around bottom face ending same as prior

name: Smile
description: Straight up and out

name: Bored
description: Labeled 3 in photo, kids dirty.

name: Bored’s brother boredom
description: Kinda dirty, but better than prior.

name: Chuckie’s chop sticks
description: Traverses obvious ledge into finger crack, depending if you top before or after the corner varies number grade. Labeled 2.

name: Dark alley rails
description: Starts on bottom of narrow corridor utilizing the top rail for hands and feet above the obvious line up the middle, quality and fun to do laps on...

name: A long walk on a hot day
description: Left pinch right sloper start in small corner, up and out

name: Drag those feet
description: Weird, awkward loose line...

name: Easy peas
description: traverse rail till it ends then top out.

name: Peas direct
description: Start under the finish to east peas, climb up and out.

name: Ready, set,  brush
description: Same start as prior, traverse left after pulling up off of ground to the top of area to the left...

name: Scars build confidence
description: Start directly under the right side of 5 ft scar from rock fall. Climb up and slightly left to top out in the middle of scar.

name: Wounded elbows
description: More solid than its counter part, straight up.

name: Wounded knees
description: Watch for loose rock, straight up and out.

name: Flash
description: Hand crack

name: Homage of no understanding
description: Sit start on micro ledge, surpass the vertical micro slopper of misery and traverse up and left to top...

name: Missourian Flake
description: Climb obvious offwidth flake up and out...

name: The Missourian
description: Same start as prior traverse left up and out on ledges...

name: Petpieve “nanny’s voice” talk through your mouth woman
description: Straight up, decent, solid rock...

name: Pipe dream
description: Hands on rail, feet on face below, ledges don’t count...

name: Running late for mass
description: Sit start up the Missourian flake then traverse rail to right topping just after the beginning to old homage...

name: Silly boy, climbing is for billy goats...
description: Same start as prior, traverse the other way to tallest point...

name: Stock in Phillip Morris
description: Start at the end of rail in prior route, traverse up and left to top.

name: Ticks, mosquitos, and snakes oh my
description: Traverses rail 7/10 th’s the way to top from left side of homage wall the distance of wall to top out same as old homage... fun running laps on

name: Whisker fish can have a attitude...
description: Straight up...

name: “Old Homage”
description: Nail biting good! Obvious line that traverses face to right, getting kinda low on micro ledge toward end after the vertical sloper of death. Tops at the highest point.  Classic, on stellar rock!

name: Creating
description: Sit start on right topping middle. Crispy.

name: Lil’s little pockets
description: Very easy line of pockets sit start.

name: Private Chucks aspirations
description: Left to right topping on right, top rail don’t count... many variations exist, not including pockets increases a number or two on the grade.

name: Deffinetly not a crack in the earth
description: Funky sit start...

name: Juniors way
description: Starts with two slopers on the right side of slab, traverses left only utilizing 1st hold identifiable by chalk on top rail, then follows a very distinct line of crimps and mono pockets to the top left of slab. Quality bouldering in Ks....

name: Licking
description: Sit start acquiring layback crimps. Up and little left finishing above 2 pad dimple..

name: Long legs and blonde hair...
description: Traverses middle section of Juniors way start same as prior.

name: Practical nonsense
description: Sit start, on flake. Up and out.

name: Prominence
description: Sit start under hollow sounding bulge. One of the first routes here back in 2000.

name: Uber this
description: Sit start on crimps(kinda reach). Up and left to finish in the middle of juniors way.

name: An Indians indirect arete
description: Climbs the tall arete, deffinetly a crack in the rock and not the earth... still worth while!

name: Ashes
description: Fave just left of arete

name: Chopstix
description: utilize jugs above blocked roof, traverse right to prominent rail, then up and right to top of the arete.

name: Double double undercling
description: Climb across face under roofs on left, to the right accessing the line of 5 under clings running to the arete on right side of the tallest part of wall. Top the arete.

name: Duplicate
description: Sit start under right side of over hang, straight up and out.

name: Jagged
description: Left of narrow vertical slot in middle of wall, top left side of giant flake laying on top.

name: Left
description: Left side of arete

name: Middle
description: Straight up the middle

name: Old gheezer
description: Up and over blocks on left side.

name: Picking your big nose
description: left side of overhang, sit start on undercling then straight up.

name: President Chubby Direct
description: Just left of prior. Utilize left side pull to acces crimp with right, pull left up to three finger slopey pocket then dyno to top rail. Very fun, and exposed at top, if you miss dyno, it is a long fall but well spotted with 2 pads.

name: Rail of death
description: Top rail from chimney to working righ over overhang and topping before you reach the taller section of wall. Feet on face are out, utilize the thin rail on underside of overhang...

name: Razorback
description: Start on right side of tallest face on tall wall. Traverse diagonally left to top.

name: Right
description: Right side of small arete

name: Romage
description: Straight up on good holds, avoid two rocks vertically  in slot, usually have x’s on them.

name: Top rail express
description: Traverse top rail from left to right.

name: Traversified
description: Traverse left on Thin crimps on face above overhang, then wondering up and left to top on the tallest section of rock.

name: Wheezers
description: Traverse jugs to top before overhang

name: A rainy day gone good...
description: Starts 6 ft left of growls on unique holds, traverses left to access the corner just past the finish to “I love you Saint Rose”, climb up through the steep ground to access and top the corner.

name: Awkward
description: Awkwardly loose rock, makes for a unique experience... straight up and out.

name: Dirty paws
description: Climbs up to the break in the rail then slightly right..

name: Dynosaurous
description: Weird layback with funky feet, builds for dyno to the rail, then up and out...

name: Farewell to Texas
description: Start on corner via sitting and laying back on crimps, traverse right, following distinct rail of crimps to bring you to the dyno move, throw the dyno, then move right to top the same as prior.

name: Growl
description: Starts just left of the strange gape, on thin holds to access rail, then up to some dicey moves above overhang, two pads recommended...

name: I love you Saint Rose
description: Starts the same as ready set brush, Accra the rail above the overhang,  then traverse left until the rail disappears into a finger crack, follow finger crack until it turns into a rail then finish up the arete at the end.  It has been done with feet up high and below overhang, rating feels the same both ways.  Very enjoyable, and a endurance run for sure...

name: Married in a month, say what?
description: Start around the corner, follow the series of ledges to top out the same as “I love you Saint Rose”.

name: Of copper heads and brooms...
description: Start same as prior, after getting hands above steep ground traverse left to prowl and top out...  Day of first ascent a epic battle took place with a broom and a monster copper head, unexpectedly.

name: Of providence or man
description: Just right of the strange opening in rock, crimps to rail then right and out.

name: Scrutinies
description: Straight up the finish of prior...

name: Steady as she goes
description: Slopey start, dyno to jug, straight up and out.

name: The strange gape...
description: Climb over the strange gape, up and out.... Super fun!
